Package edu.ntu.bto.control

Class ManagerControl

java.lang.Object
edu.ntu.bto.control.ManagerControl
public class ManagerControl extends Object
Control class for HDB Manager operations. ManagerControl allows managers to create/edit/delete projects, approve or reject applications and withdrawal requests, approve or reject officer registrations, and generate summary reports.
Author:
SC2002 Assignment Group

  • Method Details

    • createProject

      public void createProject(String name, String neighborhood, String type1, int unitsType1, double priceType1, String type2, int unitsType2, double priceType2, String openDate, String closeDate, String manager)
      Creates a new project with the given details and adds it to the system.
      Parameters:
      name - The project name.
      neighborhood - The project neighborhood.
      type1 - The first flat type.
      unitsType1 - Number of units for flat type 1.
      priceType1 - Price for flat type 1.
      type2 - The second flat type (can be empty or "N/A" if none).
      unitsType2 - Number of units for flat type 2.
      priceType2 - Price for flat type 2.
      openDate - Application opening date.
      closeDate - Application closing date.
      manager - The manager identifier (name or NRIC) for this project.

    • editProject

      public void editProject(Project project, String name, String neighborhood, String type1, int unitsType1, double priceType1, String type2, int unitsType2, double priceType2, String openDate, String closeDate, String manager, int officerSlot, String officer)
      Edits the details of an existing project. All provided new values will replace the current attributes of the project.
      Parameters:
      project - The Project to edit.
      name - The new project name.
      neighborhood - The new neighborhood.
      type1 - The new flat type 1 name.
      unitsType1 - The new number of units for flat type 1.
      priceType1 - The new price for flat type 1.
      type2 - The new flat type 2 name.
      unitsType2 - The new number of units for flat type 2.
      priceType2 - The new price for flat type 2.
      openDate - The new opening date.
      closeDate - The new closing date.
      manager - The manager identifier (likely unchanged).
      officerSlot - The new officer slot count.
      officer - The officer identifier (likely unchanged).

    • deleteProject

      public void deleteProject(Project project)
      Deletes a project from the system. All associated data (applications, registrations, etc.) should be considered invalid after removal.
      Parameters:
      project - The Project to delete.

    • approveApplication

      public void approveApplication(Application app)
      Approves an applicant's application for a flat. The application status is set to SUCCESSFUL if there are flats available for the requested flat type, and one unit is reserved (decremented from available count).
      Parameters:
      app - The Application to approve.

    • rejectApplication

      public void rejectApplication(Application app)
      Rejects an applicant's application. The application status is set to UNSUCCESSFUL, allowing the applicant to possibly apply for another project.
      Parameters:
      app - The Application to reject.

    • approveWithdrawal

      public void approveWithdrawal(Applicant applicant)
      Approves an applicant's request to withdraw their application. The application is marked as UNSUCCESSFUL (canceled). If the application was previously successful and a unit was reserved, that unit could be made available again.
      Parameters:
      applicant - The applicant requesting withdrawal.

    • rejectWithdrawal

      public void rejectWithdrawal(Applicant applicant)
      Rejects an applicant's request to withdraw their application. The application remains in its current state (e.g., still active or successful).
      Parameters:
      applicant - The applicant requesting withdrawal.

    • approveOfficer

      public void approveOfficer(Registration reg)
      Approves an HDB Officer's registration request to handle a project. The registration status is updated to APPROVED, the project is updated to assign the officer, and the officer slot count is decremented.
      Parameters:
      reg - The Registration to approve.

    • rejectOfficer

      public void rejectOfficer(Registration reg)
      Rejects an HDB Officer's registration request to handle a project. The registration status is updated to REJECTED.
      Parameters:
      reg - The Registration to reject.

    • generateReport

      public void generateReport(String filterBy)
      Generates a report of applicants with booked flats. Currently, this method prints out a list of all applications that have status BOOKED. The filterBy parameter is not dynamically used in this implementation.
      Parameters:
      filterBy - A filter criteria for the report (e.g., "BOOKED" to filter applications that are booked).
